data.enText: to a fairly large degree, especially in comparison to sth else
data.chText: 相当程度上；相当地；相对地

data.enText: I found the test relatively easy.
data.chText: 我觉得这次测试比较容易。

data.enText: We had relatively few applications for the job.
data.chText: 申请我们这项工作的人相对较少。

data.enText: Lack of exercise is also a risk factor for heart disease but it's relatively small when compared with the others.
data.chText: 缺乏锻炼也是导致心脏病的一个因素。但和其他因素相比，这种危险较小。

data.enText: used when you are comparing sth with all similar things
data.chText: （和所有类似事物比较）相对而言

data.enText: Relatively speaking, these jobs provide good salaries.
data.chText: 相对来说，这些工作报酬都不低。

value.def: Relatively means to a certain degree, especially when compared with other things of the same kind.
value.tran: 相对而言;比较起来;某种程度上
